    "headerDoc": "STEP 941 — Weak Tao 2019: Almost-All Collatz Formalization\n  藤本伸樹 2026-04-21\n\n  Source: Terence Tao (2019) — \"Almost all Collatz orbits attain almost bounded values\"\n  arXiv:1909.03562, Forum of Mathematics, Pi 10 (2022).\n\n  TAO'S THEOREM (informal):\n    For almost all n (in the sense of natural density), the Collatz orbit of n\n    enters (−∞, f(n)] for any f: N→R with f(n)→∞.\n\n  More precisely: For any function f: N → R with f(n) → ∞,\n    lim_{N→∞} (1/N) · #{n ≤ N : min_{k≥0} iterC k n ≤ f(n)} = 1\n\n  In D-FUMT₈ terms: The set of n where Collatz fails is ZERO-measure (value: 4.0).\n\n  THIS FILE"
  },
